7&amp;nbsp; First created were the druids, for they were all&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
women and beautiful to behold.&amp;nbsp; They were given &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
leather and large busts.&amp;nbsp; And the Vision saw it was &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Gu-ud.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
8&amp;nbsp; Next came the shaman and they were made in &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
the image of barbarians of the north.&amp;nbsp; Tall, strong &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
and possessing amazing cleavage, these women&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
would help keep the cold at bay.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
9 Then did the Vision reach an epiphany and said&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
"I need warriors", thus the class description was &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
created-&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Warriors shall be the masters of armed combat and defense, takign the&#xD;
point in battles and going head to head with the most dangerous&#xD;
creatures of Norrath.&amp;nbsp; Warriors are a melee class with the ability&#xD;
to wear plate armor and wield all types of weapons.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Warriors build their strength and stamine to unheard of levels, making&#xD;
them far hardier than any other class.&amp;nbsp; When combined with their&#xD;
heavy armor and excellent defensive skills, warriors are unmatched in&#xD;
tehir ability to survive the most brutal battles.&amp;nbsp; Warriors train&#xD;
themselves in the skills of combat, mastering teh use of all weapons&#xD;
and tactics.&amp;nbsp; Warriors also learn to taunt their opponents, making&#xD;
themselves the focus of all their enemies' attacks, allowing the less&#xD;
resilient members of their group to remain safe from harm.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
